<div id="review_2596855778" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2596855778" />
    <a title="Lucas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/89439546-lucas"><img alt="Lucas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1567567144p2/89439546.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2596855778?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lucas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lucas" href="/user/show/89439546-lucas">Lucas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89439546-lucas?shelf=kids-books-dragons">kids-books-dragons</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89439546-lucas?shelf=kids-books-9-12">kids-books-9-12</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89439546-lucas?shelf=children-magic-books">children-magic-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89439546-lucas?shelf=best-kids-books-ever">best-kids-books-ever</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89439546-lucas?shelf=grades-4-6">grades-4-6</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89439546-lucas?shelf=children-fantasy-books">children-fantasy-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2596855778" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4279092798322838123">I saw an ad for this book somewhere online that said: Caution, may contain magic. And I think it totally sums up the book. A magical journey, with a ton a really good humor.<br/>The magic in Archibald Finch is truly amazing, but the way I see it, it&apos;s not really because of the actual magic inside (the secret underworld, the fantastic creatures, the witches&apos; weapons, etc.) but more because of the incredible atmosphere (so mysterious and eerie), that shrouds the story. Or should I say the stories, sinc</span>
  <span id="freeText4279092798322838123" style="display:none">I saw an ad for this book somewhere online that said: Caution, may contain magic. And I think it totally sums up the book. A magical journey, with a ton a really good humor.<br />The magic in Archibald Finch is truly amazing, but the way I see it, it's not really because of the actual magic inside (the secret underworld, the fantastic creatures, the witches' weapons, etc.) but more because of the incredible atmosphere (so mysterious and eerie), that shrouds the story. Or should I say the stories, since there are actually two distinct stories, which even though they are unfolding in different worlds (our almost normal world of 2018, and a definitely less normal world of way back then, in the Dark Ages...)<br />About half of the chapters take place in one world. And the other half in the other. And just for the record, there's no better half. What's actually interesting is that at first you wonder which world you prefer (For me it was Lemurea), until you realize (around chapter 6) how intertwined those two worlds are, and how they co-exist and work together to help us make sense of things. It all ends up reading as one story. And that might be the most magical thing of all.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4279092798322838123" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

